  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type the transformation acts on. This will often correspond to the transformed column's data type.

    All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataTableTransformation, MutatingDataTableTransformation
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BasicRowWiseColumnTransformation, ContextlessRowWiseColumnTransformation

    public abstract class FunctionRowWiseColumnTransformation<T,C>
extends ContextualRowWiseColumnTransformation<T,C>
    The FunctionRowWiseColumnTransformation is a contextual row-wise column transformation where the transformed values are calculated via a function acting on the initial value of the column and the data row being transformed.

                                   Function2<T,C,T> transformation)
        Constructor specifying the column to transform, the data type the transformation acts on, and the function which will calculate the transformation values.
        Parameters:
        column - The name of the column this transformation will act on.
        dataType - The type the transformation acts on. If this does not correspond to the type of data held by column, the the data table will probably need to have data coercion enabled.
        transformation - The function which will transform the original column value. The initial column value and the context are passed to this function as arguments.

      • FunctionRowWiseColumnTransformation

        protected FunctionRowWiseColumnTransformation(java.lang.String column,
                                   Function2<T,C,T> transformation)
        Constructor specifying the column to transform and the function which will calculate the transformation values. The data type this transformation acts on will be the same as the type of the column in the data table.
        Parameters:
        column - The name of the column this transformation will act on.
        transformation - The function which will transform the original column value. The initial column value and the context are passed to this function as arguments.
